"title": "4604: animals, nature of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4604",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>As a class within the created order, their variety reflects God's generous giving. He makes human beings their stewards, though they themselves come into the category of creatures.</p>\n<h2>Animals in their profusion</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:24-Gen1:25\">GEN 1:24–1:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen7:1-Gen7:3\">GEN 7:1–7:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen7:13-Gen7:16\">GEN 7:13–7:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen8:15-Gen8:19\">GEN 8:15–8:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps50:9-Ps50:11\">PSA 50:9–50:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps148:7-Ps148:10\">PSA 148:7–148:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:20\">ISA 43:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek36:11\">EZK 36:11</a></p>\n<h2>Animals as illustrated by their variety</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:6-Isa11:8\">ISA 11:6–11:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:12\">EXO 23:12</a> <em>Ox, donkey</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:3-Exod25:5\">EXO 25:3–25:5</a> <em>Goat, sea cow</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:4-Lev11:7\">LEV 11:4–11:7</a> <em>Rabbit, pig</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:29-Lev11:30\">LEV 11:29–11:30</a> <em>Weasel, rat</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:2\">NUM 19:2</a> <em>Heifer</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut14:4-Deut14:5\">DEU 14:4–14:5</a> <em>Deer, gazelle, antelope</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:34-1Sam17:35\">1SA 17:34–17:35</a> <em>Sheep, bear, lion</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job40:15-Job40:24\">JOB 40:15–40:24</a> <em>possibly the hippopotamus</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job41:1-Job41:34\">JOB 41:1–41:34</a> <em>possibly the crocodile</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps58:4\">PSA 58:4</a> <em>Snake</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps105:30\">PSA 105:30</a> <em>Frog</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song2:15\">SNG 2:15</a> <em>Fox</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa13:21-Isa13:22\">ISA 13:21–13:22</a> <em>Jackal, wild goat, hyena</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa51:8\">ISA 51:8</a> <em>Worm</em></p>\n<h2>Human beings within the animal creation</h2>\n<h3>As part of creation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:7\">GEN 2:7</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl3:18-Eccl3:21\">ECC 3:18–3:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps49:12\">PSA 49:12</a></p>\n<h3>Significantly different from the rest of creation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:26-Gen1:27\">GEN 1:26–1:27</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Human beings as stewards of the animal kingdom</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps8:6-Ps8:8\">PSA 8:6–8:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:26-Gen1:28\">GEN 1:26–1:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:19-Gen2:20\">GEN 2:19–2:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen9:1-Gen9:2\">GEN 9:1–9:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:6-Heb2:8\">HEB 2:6–2:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:7-Jas3:8\">JAS 3:7–3:8</a></p>\n<h2>Animals as the objects of divine, and therefore human, care</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen9:8-Gen9:10\">GEN 9:8–9:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen8:1\">GEN 8:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod9:4-Exod9:6\">EXO 9:4–9:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs3:17\">2KI 3:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job5:23\">JOB 5:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job38:39-Job38:41\">JOB 38:39–38:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job39:1-Job39:30\">JOB 39:1–39:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps104:20-Ps104:21\">PSA 104:20–104:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov12:10\">PRO 12:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov27:23\">PRO 27:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:22\">JOL 2:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah4:11\">JON 4:11</a></p>\n<h2>Animals and Noah's ark</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen7:13-Gen7:23\">GEN 7:13–7:23</a></p>",
